commit.message: KDbg 3.1.0.
Update German translation.
Update translation files.
Extend copyright to 2023.

Move old release notes out of the way.

Having many not very relevant files at the top-level of the project does
not look right. Move release notes into their own directory.

Merge branch 'maint'

* maint:
  Recognize "<incomplete type>" after a reference address.

Merge branch 'gcc-13' of https://github.com/hartwork/kdbg-fork

* 'gcc-13' of https://github.com/hartwork/kdbg-fork:
  linux.yml: Add GCC 9 to the mix
  linux.yml: Upgrade from GCC 12 to GCC 13

linux.yml: Add GCC 9 to the mix

The idea is to cover not only modern but also more ancient
compilers, and GCC 9 is the oldest we can economically
cover with GitHub Actions CI images.

linux.yml: Upgrade from GCC 12 to GCC 13

Compilers are getting stricter and stricter and we want
to be sure to not introduce changes that would break
compilation with GCC 13.

Merge branch 'issue-5-fix-icon-installation-target' of https://github.com/hartwork/kdbg-fork

* 'issue-5-fix-icon-installation-target' of https://github.com/hartwork/kdbg-fork:
  Rename icon "document-open-executable" to "executable-open"
  kdbg/pics/CMakeLists.txt: Fix icon installation target location

Rename icon "document-open-executable" to "executable-open"

With the old name "document-open-executable", a theme that
provided more a generic icon "document-open" or "document"
would win over more specific icon "document-open-executable"
of KDbg, as documented at
https://specifications.freedesktop.org/icon-naming-spec/icon-naming-spec-latest.html#guidelines .
The new name ensures that KDbg's custom icon is used.

Fully automated with commands:
$ git grep -l document-open-executable | xargs sed 's,document-open-executable,executable-open,g' -i
$ git mv kdbg/pics/16-actions-{document-open-executable,executable-open}.png
$ git mv kdbg/pics/22-actions-{document-open-executable,executable-open}.png
$ git mv kdbg/pics/32-actions-{document-open-executable,executable-open}.png
$ git mv kdbg/pics/48-actions-{document-open-executable,executable-open}.png
$ git mv kdbg/pics/sc-actions-{document-open-executable,executable-open}.svg
Add simple CI based on GitHub Actions

Do not hard-code Qt5 installation paths in kdbg/testprogs/Makefile.

We are going to add CI support, and will do it in such a way that
it also compiles the files in kdbg/testprogs. However, the CI system's
Qt5 libraries are installed in locations different from those expected
by the Makefile. Use qmake to derive the installation paths.

Co-authored-by: Johannes Sixt <j6t@kdbg.org>

kdbg/main.cpp: Stop adding --version, --help, --help-all twice

Symptom was:
> # kdbg --version
> QCommandLineParser: already having an option named "h"
> QCommandLineParser: already having an option named "help-all"
> QCommandLineParser: already having an option named "v"
> kdbg 3.0.1

KAboutData::setupCommandLine is already adding these for us,
so no need to add them again, ourselves.

Related docs:
https://api.kde.org/frameworks/kcoreaddons/html/classKAboutData.html#afaf16b9be9deacfe10669219c50f2b43

Recognize "<incomplete type>" after a reference address.

A reference to an object with incomplete type is printed like this:

   fmt = @0x7fffffffd620: <incomplete type>

The parser understands only a restricted set of notices after the reference
address. Hence, such a value confuses the parser. Make this case known.
